summary: Title: The Cottage Summary: There was a cottage on the hill on the Isle of Man that he loved. It had been beautiful at one point...
body:
Title: The Cottage

Summary: There was a cottage on the hill on the Isle of Man that he loved. It had been beautiful at one point in history. Crisp white siding, a bright red door with roofing to match, large windows and a beautiful garden surrounding the path from the gate to the doorway. He always wanted it to be his one day.

Excerpt:

Dan all but strained his neck leaning in to kiss him. “I leave. It’s what I do and it’s why I’m single right now. It’s hard to love someone who is never around.”

Phil’s lip quivered. Knowing that Dan felt that way, that someone else made him feel that way when Dan never deserved it. He had a job and a passion. He does what he loves and somehow that’s made it hard for people to love him.

“I’d still find a way to love you if you moved to China,” he said softly so that the tears didn’t come.

Chapter 6

From the beginning
